Ngati
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:(i) occasionally used for the local people or tangata whenua: 'the Ngati have placed a temporary prohibition on the use of this road.' (ii) (transferred use) a brumby, wild Maori horse (chiefly of the central North Island plateau)
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
